26/* TODO: for functions with mpz_srcptr, check whether mpz_fits_slong_p
27 is really useful in all cases. For instance, concerning the addition,
28 one now has mpz_t -> long -> unsigned long -> mpfr_t then mpfr_add
29 instead of mpz_t -> mpfr_t then mpfr_add. */

31/* Init and set a mpfr_t with enough precision to store a mpz.
32 This function should be called in the extended exponent range. */
33static void
34init_set_z (mpfr_ptr t, mpz_srcptr z)
35{
36 mpfr_prec_t p;
37 int i;
38
39 if (mpz_size (z) <= 1)
40 p = GMP_NUMB_BITS;
41 else
42 MPFR_MPZ_SIZEINBASE2 (p, z);
43 mpfr_init2 (t, p);
44 i = mpfr_set_z (t, z, MPFR_RNDN);
45 /* Possible assertion failure in case of overflow. Such cases,
46 which imply that z is huge (if the function is called in
47 the extended exponent range), are currently not supported,
48 just like precisions around MPFR_PREC_MAX. */
49 MPFR_ASSERTN (i == 0); (void) i; /* use i to avoid a warning */
50}
51
52/* Init, set a mpfr_t with enough precision to store a mpz_t without round,
53 call the function, and clear the allocated mpfr_t */
54static int
55foo (mpfr_ptr x, mpfr_srcptr y, mpz_srcptr z, mpfr_rnd_t r,
56 int (*f)(mpfr_ptr, mpfr_srcptr, mpfr_srcptr, mpfr_rnd_t))
57{
58 mpfr_t t;
59 int i;
60 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_DECL (expo);
61
62 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_MARK (expo);
63 init_set_z (t, z); /* There should be no exceptions. */
64 i = (*f) (x, y, t, r);
65 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_UPDATE_FLAGS (expo, __gmpfr_flags);
66 mpfr_clear (t);
67 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_FREE (expo);
68 return mpfr_check_range (x, i, r);
69}
70
71static int
72foo2 (mpfr_ptr x, mpz_srcptr y, mpfr_srcptr z, mpfr_rnd_t r,
73 int (*f)(mpfr_ptr, mpfr_srcptr, mpfr_srcptr, mpfr_rnd_t))
74{
75 mpfr_t t;
76 int i;
77 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_DECL (expo);
78
79 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_MARK (expo);
80 init_set_z (t, y); /* There should be no exceptions. */
81 i = (*f) (x, t, z, r);
82 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_UPDATE_FLAGS (expo, __gmpfr_flags);
83 mpfr_clear (t);
84 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_FREE (expo);
85 return mpfr_check_range (x, i, r);
86}

88int
89mpfr_mul_z (mpfr_ptr y, mpfr_srcptr x, mpz_srcptr z, mpfr_rnd_t r)
90{
91 if (mpz_fits_slong_p (z))
92 return mpfr_mul_si (y, x, mpz_get_si (z), r);
93 else
94 return foo (y, x, z, r, mpfr_mul);
95}

97int
98mpfr_div_z (mpfr_ptr y, mpfr_srcptr x, mpz_srcptr z, mpfr_rnd_t r)
99{
100 if (mpz_fits_slong_p (z))
101 return mpfr_div_si (y, x, mpz_get_si (z), r);
102 else
103 return foo (y, x, z, r, mpfr_div);
104}

107mpfr_add_z (mpfr_ptr y, mpfr_srcptr x, mpz_srcptr z, mpfr_rnd_t r)

109 if (mpz_fits_slong_p (z))
110 return mpfr_add_si (y, x, mpz_get_si (z), r);

112 return foo (y, x, z, r, mpfr_add);

116mpfr_sub_z (mpfr_ptr y, mpfr_srcptr x, mpz_srcptr z, mpfr_rnd_t r)

118 if (mpz_fits_slong_p (z))
119 return mpfr_sub_si (y, x, mpz_get_si (z), r);

121 return foo (y, x, z, r, mpfr_sub);

124int
125mpfr_z_sub (mpfr_ptr y, mpz_srcptr x, mpfr_srcptr z, mpfr_rnd_t r)
126{
127 if (mpz_fits_slong_p (x))
128 return mpfr_si_sub (y, mpz_get_si (x), z, r);
129 else
130 return foo2 (y, x, z, r, mpfr_sub);
131}
132
133int
134mpfr_cmp_z (mpfr_srcptr x, mpz_srcptr z)
135{
136 mpfr_t t;
137 int res;
138 mpfr_prec_t p;
139 mpfr_flags_t flags;
140
141 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (MPFR_IS_SINGULAR (x)))
142 return mpfr_cmp_si (x, mpz_sgn (z));
143
144 if (mpz_fits_slong_p (z))
145 return mpfr_cmp_si (x, mpz_get_si (z));
146
147 if (mpz_size (z) <= 1)
148 p = GMP_NUMB_BITS;
149 else
150 MPFR_MPZ_SIZEINBASE2 (p, z);
151 mpfr_init2 (t, p);
152 flags = __gmpfr_flags;
153 if (mpfr_set_z (t, z, MPFR_RNDN))
154 {
155 /* overflow (t is an infinity) or underflow */
156 mpfr_div_2ui (t, t, 2, MPFR_RNDZ); /* if underflow, set t to zero */
157 __gmpfr_flags = flags; /* restore the flags */
158 /* The real value of t (= z), which falls outside the exponent range,
159 has been replaced by an equivalent value for the comparison: zero
160 or an infinity. */
161 }
162 res = mpfr_cmp (x, t);
163 mpfr_clear (t);
164 return res;
165}

167#ifndef MPFR_USE_MINI_GMP
168/* Compute y = RND(x*n/d), where n and d are mpz integers.
169 An integer 0 is assumed to have a positive sign.
170 This function is used by mpfr_mul_q and mpfr_div_q.
171 Note: the status of the rational 0/(-1) is not clear (if there is
172 a signed infinity, there should be a signed zero). But infinities
173 are not currently supported/documented in GMP, and if the rational
174 is canonicalized as it should be, the case 0/(-1) cannot occur. */
175static int
176mpfr_muldiv_z (mpfr_ptr y, mpfr_srcptr x, mpz_srcptr n, mpz_srcptr d,
177 mpfr_rnd_t rnd_mode)
178{
179 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (mpz_sgn (n) == 0))
180 {
181 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (mpz_sgn (d) == 0))
182 MPFR_SET_NAN (y);
183 else
184 {
185 mpfr_mul_ui (y, x, 0, MPFR_RNDN); /* exact: +0, -0 or NaN */
186 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (mpz_sgn (d) < 0))
187 MPFR_CHANGE_SIGN (y);
188 }
189 return 0;
190 }
191 else if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (mpz_sgn (d) == 0))
192 {
193 mpfr_div_ui (y, x, 0, MPFR_RNDN); /* exact: +Inf, -Inf or NaN */
194 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (mpz_sgn (n) < 0))
195 MPFR_CHANGE_SIGN (y);
196 return 0;
197 }
198 else
199 {
200 mpfr_prec_t p;
201 mpfr_t tmp;
202 int inexact;
203 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_DECL (expo);
204
205 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_MARK (expo);
206
207 /* With the current MPFR code, using mpfr_mul_z and mpfr_div_z
208 for the general case should be faster than doing everything
209 in mpn, mpz and/or mpq. MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_MARK could be avoided
210 here, but it would be more difficult to handle corner cases. */
211 MPFR_MPZ_SIZEINBASE2 (p, n);
212 mpfr_init2 (tmp, MPFR_PREC (x) + p);
213 inexact = mpfr_mul_z (tmp, x, n, MPFR_RNDN);
214 /* Since |n| >= 1, an underflow is not possible. And the precision of
215 tmp has been chosen so that inexact != 0 iff there's an overflow. */
216 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (inexact != 0))
217 {
218 mpfr_t x0;
219 mpfr_exp_t ex;
220 MPFR_BLOCK_DECL (flags);
221
222 /* intermediate overflow case */
223 MPFR_ASSERTD (mpfr_inf_p (tmp));
224 ex = MPFR_GET_EXP (x); /* x is a pure FP number */
225 MPFR_ALIAS (x0, x, MPFR_SIGN(x), 0); /* x0 = x / 2^ex */
226 MPFR_BLOCK (flags,
227 inexact = mpfr_mul_z (tmp, x0, n, MPFR_RNDN);
228 MPFR_ASSERTD (inexact == 0);
229 inexact = mpfr_div_z (y, tmp, d, rnd_mode);
230 /* Just in case the division underflows
231 (highly unlikely, not supported)... */
232 MPFR_ASSERTN (!MPFR_BLOCK_EXCEP));
233 MPFR_EXP (y) += ex;
234 /* Detect highly unlikely, not supported corner cases... */
235 MPFR_ASSERTN (MPFR_EXP (y) >= __gmpfr_emin);
236 MPFR_ASSERTN (! MPFR_IS_SINGULAR (y));
237 /* The potential overflow will be detected by mpfr_check_range. */
238 }
239 else
240 inexact = mpfr_div_z (y, tmp, d, rnd_mode);
241
242 mpfr_clear (tmp);
243
244 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_FREE (expo);
245 return mpfr_check_range (y, inexact, rnd_mode);
246 }
247}
248
249int
250mpfr_mul_q (mpfr_ptr y, mpfr_srcptr x, mpq_srcptr z, mpfr_rnd_t rnd_mode)
251{
252 return mpfr_muldiv_z (y, x, mpq_numref (z), mpq_denref (z), rnd_mode);
253}
254
255int
256mpfr_div_q (mpfr_ptr y, mpfr_srcptr x, mpq_srcptr z, mpfr_rnd_t rnd_mode)
257{
258 return mpfr_muldiv_z (y, x, mpq_denref (z), mpq_numref (z), rnd_mode);
259}
260
261int
262mpfr_add_q (mpfr_ptr y, mpfr_srcptr x, mpq_srcptr z, mpfr_rnd_t rnd_mode)
263{
264 mpfr_t t,q;
265 mpfr_prec_t p;
266 mpfr_exp_t err;
267 int res;
268 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_DECL (expo);
269 MPFR_ZIV_DECL (loop);
270
271 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (MPFR_IS_SINGULAR (x)))
272 {
273 if (MPFR_IS_NAN (x))
274 {
275 MPFR_SET_NAN (y);
276 MPFR_RET_NAN;
277 }
278 else if (MPFR_IS_INF (x))
279 {
280 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (mpz_sgn (mpq_denref (z)) == 0 &&
281 MPFR_MULT_SIGN (mpz_sgn (mpq_numref (z)),
282 MPFR_SIGN (x)) <= 0))
283 {
284 MPFR_SET_NAN (y);
285 MPFR_RET_NAN;
286 }
287 MPFR_SET_INF (y);
288 MPFR_SET_SAME_SIGN (y, x);
289 MPFR_RET (0);
290 }
291 else
292 {
293 MPFR_ASSERTD (MPFR_IS_ZERO (x));
294 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (mpq_sgn (z) == 0))
295 return mpfr_set (y, x, rnd_mode); /* signed 0 - Unsigned 0 */
296 else
297 return mpfr_set_q (y, z, rnd_mode);
298 }
299 }
300
301 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_MARK (expo);
302
303 p = MPFR_PREC (y) + 10;
304 mpfr_init2 (t, p);
305 mpfr_init2 (q, p);
306
307 MPFR_ZIV_INIT (loop, p);
308 for (;;)
309 {
310 MPFR_BLOCK_DECL (flags);
311
312 res = mpfr_set_q (q, z, MPFR_RNDN); /* Error <= 1/2 ulp(q) */
313 /* If z if @INF@ (1/0), res = 0, so it quits immediately */
314 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (res == 0))
315 /* Result is exact so we can add it directly! */
316 {
317 res = mpfr_add (y, x, q, rnd_mode);
318 break;
319 }
320 MPFR_BLOCK (flags, mpfr_add (t, x, q, MPFR_RNDN));
321 /* Error on t is <= 1/2 ulp(t), except in case of overflow/underflow,
322 but such an exception is very unlikely as it would be possible
323 only if q has a huge numerator or denominator. Not supported! */
324 MPFR_ASSERTN (! (MPFR_OVERFLOW (flags) || MPFR_UNDERFLOW (flags)));
325 /* Error / ulp(t) <= 1/2 + 1/2 * 2^(EXP(q)-EXP(t))
326 If EXP(q)-EXP(t)>0, <= 2^(EXP(q)-EXP(t)-1)*(1+2^-(EXP(q)-EXP(t)))
327 <= 2^(EXP(q)-EXP(t))
328 If EXP(q)-EXP(t)<0, <= 2^0 */
329 /* We can get 0, but we can't round since q is inexact */
330 if (MPFR_LIKELY (!MPFR_IS_ZERO (t)))
331 {
332 err = (mpfr_exp_t) p - 1 - MAX (MPFR_GET_EXP(q)-MPFR_GET_EXP(t), 0);
333 if (MPFR_LIKELY (MPFR_CAN_ROUND (t, err, MPFR_PREC (y), rnd_mode)))
334 {
335 res = mpfr_set (y, t, rnd_mode);
336 break;
337 }
338 }
339 MPFR_ZIV_NEXT (loop, p);
340 mpfr_set_prec (t, p);
341 mpfr_set_prec (q, p);
342 }
343 MPFR_ZIV_FREE (loop);
344 mpfr_clear (t);
345 mpfr_clear (q);
346
347 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_FREE (expo);
348 return mpfr_check_range (y, res, rnd_mode);
349}
350
351int
352mpfr_sub_q (mpfr_ptr y, mpfr_srcptr x, mpq_srcptr z,mpfr_rnd_t rnd_mode)
353{
354 mpfr_t t,q;
355 mpfr_prec_t p;
356 int res;
357 mpfr_exp_t err;
358 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_DECL (expo);
359 MPFR_ZIV_DECL (loop);
360
361 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (MPFR_IS_SINGULAR (x)))
362 {
363 if (MPFR_IS_NAN (x))
364 {
365 MPFR_SET_NAN (y);
366 MPFR_RET_NAN;
367 }
368 else if (MPFR_IS_INF (x))
369 {
370 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (mpz_sgn (mpq_denref (z)) == 0 &&
371 MPFR_MULT_SIGN (mpz_sgn (mpq_numref (z)),
372 MPFR_SIGN (x)) >= 0))
373 {
374 MPFR_SET_NAN (y);
375 MPFR_RET_NAN;
376 }
377 MPFR_SET_INF (y);
378 MPFR_SET_SAME_SIGN (y, x);
379 MPFR_RET (0);
380 }
381 else
382 {
383 MPFR_ASSERTD (MPFR_IS_ZERO (x));
384
385 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (mpq_sgn (z) == 0))
386 return mpfr_set (y, x, rnd_mode); /* signed 0 - Unsigned 0 */
387 else
388 {
389 res = mpfr_set_q (y, z, MPFR_INVERT_RND (rnd_mode));
390 MPFR_CHANGE_SIGN (y);
391 return -res;
392 }
393 }
394 }
395
396 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_MARK (expo);
397
398 p = MPFR_PREC (y) + 10;
399 mpfr_init2 (t, p);
400 mpfr_init2 (q, p);
401
402 MPFR_ZIV_INIT (loop, p);
403 for(;;)
404 {
405 MPFR_BLOCK_DECL (flags);
406
407 res = mpfr_set_q(q, z, MPFR_RNDN); /* Error <= 1/2 ulp(q) */
408 /* If z if @INF@ (1/0), res = 0, so it quits immediately */
409 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (res == 0))
410 /* Result is exact so we can add it directly!*/
411 {
412 res = mpfr_sub (y, x, q, rnd_mode);
413 break;
414 }
415 MPFR_BLOCK (flags, mpfr_sub (t, x, q, MPFR_RNDN));
416 /* Error on t is <= 1/2 ulp(t), except in case of overflow/underflow,
417 but such an exception is very unlikely as it would be possible
418 only if q has a huge numerator or denominator. Not supported! */
419 MPFR_ASSERTN (! (MPFR_OVERFLOW (flags) || MPFR_UNDERFLOW (flags)));
420 /* Error / ulp(t) <= 1/2 + 1/2 * 2^(EXP(q)-EXP(t))
421 If EXP(q)-EXP(t)>0, <= 2^(EXP(q)-EXP(t)-1)*(1+2^-(EXP(q)-EXP(t)))
422 <= 2^(EXP(q)-EXP(t))
423 If EXP(q)-EXP(t)<0, <= 2^0 */
424 /* We can get 0, but we can't round since q is inexact */
425 if (MPFR_LIKELY (!MPFR_IS_ZERO (t)))
426 {
427 err = (mpfr_exp_t) p - 1 - MAX (MPFR_GET_EXP(q)-MPFR_GET_EXP(t), 0);
428 res = MPFR_CAN_ROUND (t, err, MPFR_PREC (y), rnd_mode);
429 if (MPFR_LIKELY (res != 0)) /* We can round! */
430 {
431 res = mpfr_set (y, t, rnd_mode);
432 break;
433 }
434 }
435 MPFR_ZIV_NEXT (loop, p);
436 mpfr_set_prec (t, p);
437 mpfr_set_prec (q, p);
438 }
439 MPFR_ZIV_FREE (loop);
440 mpfr_clear (t);
441 mpfr_clear (q);
442
443 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_FREE (expo);
444 return mpfr_check_range (y, res, rnd_mode);
445}

447int
448mpfr_cmp_q (mpfr_srcptr x, mpq_srcptr q)
449{
450 mpfr_t t;
451 int res;
452 mpfr_prec_t p;
453 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_DECL (expo);
454
455 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (mpq_denref (q) == 0))
456 {
457 /* q is an infinity or NaN */
458 mpfr_init2 (t, 2);
459 mpfr_set_q (t, q, MPFR_RNDN);
460 res = mpfr_cmp (x, t);
461 mpfr_clear (t);
462 return res;
463 }
464
465 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (MPFR_IS_SINGULAR (x)))
466 return mpfr_cmp_si (x, mpq_sgn (q));
467
468 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_MARK (expo);
469
470 /* x < a/b ? <=> x*b < a */
471 MPFR_MPZ_SIZEINBASE2 (p, mpq_denref (q));
472 mpfr_init2 (t, MPFR_PREC(x) + p);
473 res = mpfr_mul_z (t, x, mpq_denref (q), MPFR_RNDN);
474 MPFR_ASSERTD (res == 0);
475 res = mpfr_cmp_z (t, mpq_numref (q));
476 mpfr_clear (t);
477
478 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_FREE (expo);
479 return res;
480}

483#ifndef MPFR_USE_MINI_GMP
484int
485mpfr_cmp_f (mpfr_srcptr x, mpf_srcptr z)
486{
487 mpfr_t t;
488 int res;
489 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_DECL (expo);
490
491 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (MPFR_IS_SINGULAR (x)))
492 return mpfr_cmp_si (x, mpf_sgn (z));
493
494 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_MARK (expo);
495
496 mpfr_init2 (t, MPFR_PREC_MIN + ABSIZ(z) * GMP_NUMB_BITS);
497 res = mpfr_set_f (t, z, MPFR_RNDN);
498 MPFR_ASSERTD (res == 0);
499 res = mpfr_cmp (x, t);
500 mpfr_clear (t);
501
502 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_FREE (expo);
503 return res;
504}
